.TH "iio_trigger_read_current" 9 "iio_trigger_read_current" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
iio_trigger_read_current \- trigger consumer sysfs query current trigger
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" iio_trigger_read_current
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct device_attribute *attr "  ","
.BI "char *buf "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device associated with an industrial I/O device
.IP "attr" 12
pointer to the device_attribute structure that
is being processed
.IP "buf" 12
buffer where the current trigger name will be printed into
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
For trigger consumers the current_trigger interface allows the trigger
used by the device to be queried.
.SH "RETURN"
a negative number on failure, the number of characters written
on success or 0 if no trigger is available
